## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date information, as the situation is dynamic and subject to rapid changes. Additionally, the geopolitical nature of the conflict means that sources may have inherent biases based on their regional affiliations. The complexity of international relations and the involvement of multiple state and non-state actors further complicate the narrative, requiring continuous monitoring for the most accurate understanding.